Hindenburg's personal preference is the [? if dnvp_leader != "Westarp":former?] <span style="color: #3E88B3;">**DNVP**</span> leader that played a critical role in securing Hindenburg's reelection. The two has maintained contact over the past years, and share a hatred of Hugenberg. Despite this, in a meeting with Hindenburg, Westarp has declined the chancellorship and argued against dismissing Brüning, and against new elections that would destroy the German middle parties.

Even when Hindenburg was reduced to tears, a strategy that had worked on Brüning before, Westarp remains firm in his refusal. Westarp will not be the new chancellor.

